## Batch Splitting

Split input into batches using `split_jsonl_batches`:

```bash
split_jsonl_batches --input /tmp/input.jsonl --directory {{ dispatcher.agent_name }} \
  --min-batch {{ dispatcher.batch_size[0] }} --max-batch {{ dispatcher.batch_size[1] }}
```

This outputs a JSONL manifest to stdout — one line per batch:
```json
{"batch":1,"file":"/tmp/{{ dispatcher.agent_name }}/batch_001.jsonl","records":50}
```

Parse the manifest. Each line is one agent invocation.
{% endif %}

